				       ------------------
				      OfficeFloor Tutorials
				       ------------------
				      Daniel Sagenschneider
				       ------------------

OfficeFloor Tutorials

  The tutorials follow a journey from adding OfficeFloor REST composition to an existing {{{https://spring.io/projects/spring-boot}Spring Boot}} application through to running natively on OfficeFloor.

  The journey is structured as follows:

  [[1]] <<Spring Boot Entry Point>> - Add OfficeFloor REST YAML composition to your existing Spring Boot application with no migration required.

  [[2]] <<Expanding OfficeFloor Features>> - With OfficeFloor in place, incorporate reactive and polyglot functionality alongside your Spring Boot application.

  [[3]] <<Spring as Dependency Supplier>> - Begin migrating away from Spring as the web framework. OfficeFloor takes ownership of routing and composition; Spring supplies dependency-injected objects.

  [[4]] <<Native OfficeFloor>> - Spring dependency removed. Explore the full breadth of native OfficeFloor functionality: core REST, persistence, security, infrastructure, and UI.

  [[5]] <<Cloud and Deployment>> - Deploy native OfficeFloor applications to cloud platforms and cloud-native datastores.

  []

  REST endpoints are declared as YAML configuration files throughout this journey.  This allows teams to work concurrently on separate endpoint files and gives AI tooling the context it needs to generate and modify endpoint code accurately.

  The tutorials refer to <WoOF>, which stands for <Web on OfficeFloor>.  It is a set of prefabricated plug-ins for OfficeFloor that enables OfficeFloor to act as a high performance Web Application Server.  Due to {{{https://sagenschneider.blogspot.com/2019/02/inversion-of-coupling-control.html}inversion of coupling control (IOCC)}}, the prefabricated plug-ins are much more re-usable than simple Dependency Injection framework objects.

  All tutorials are part of the OfficeFloor continuous builds and their source can be found {{{http://github.com/officefloor/OfficeFloor/tree/master/officefloor/tutorials}here}}.


* Phase 1: Spring Boot Entry Point

  For developers already using Spring Boot, this is the starting point.  The {{{../officefloor-spring-boot-starter/index.html}OfficeFloor REST Spring Boot Starter}} adds REST YAML composition to your existing Spring Boot application without requiring any code migration.  Your Spring beans, security, persistence, and all other Spring configuration remain unchanged; OfficeFloor simply takes over the declaration of REST endpoints via YAML files.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
