* Phase 2: Expanding OfficeFloor Features

  With the OfficeFloor REST Spring Boot Starter in place, these tutorials show additional OfficeFloor capabilities you can incorporate while the Spring Boot foundation remains intact.  This is the phase to adopt reactive programming and polyglot procedure logic without changing anything about your existing Spring configuration.


** Reactive

  OfficeFloor's threading model integrates cleanly with reactive libraries.  These tutorials demonstrate how to wire reactive streams and reactive database clients as procedures in your REST YAML composition.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/reactive/ReactorHttpServer/index.html}Reactor}} | Integrate Project Reactor publishers and subscribers as OfficeFloor procedures. | {{{https://projectreactor.io/}Project Reactor}}\
|                                                              |                                                            | Reactive streams
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/reactive/R2dbcHttpServer/index.html}R2DBC}}    | Reactive relational database access using R2DBC within OfficeFloor REST composition. | {{{https://r2dbc.io}R2DBC}}\
|                                                              |                                                            | Reactive database
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/reactive/VertxSqlClientHttpServer/index.html}Vertx SQL Client}} | High-performance database interaction using the Vert.x SQL Client. | {{{https://github.com/eclipse-vertx/vertx-sql-client}Vertx SQL Client}}
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


** Polyglot

  OfficeFloor procedures can be written in any JVM language.  Mix Kotlin, Scala, or JavaScript logic into the same REST YAML endpoint graph as your Java Spring beans.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/KotlinHttpServer/index.html}Kotlin}}  | Implement REST procedure logic in Kotlin alongside Java procedures. | Polyglot Kotlin
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/ScalaHttpServer/index.html}Scala}}    | Implement REST procedure logic in Scala alongside Java procedures. | Polyglot Scala
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/JavaScriptHttpServer/index.html}JavaScript}} | Implement REST procedure logic in JavaScript via GraalVM. | Polyglot JavaScript\
|                                                              |                                                            | GraalVM
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/CatsHttpServer/index.html}Cats Effect}} | Integrate Cats Effect functional IO into OfficeFloor REST composition. | {{{https://typelevel.org/cats-effect/}Cats Effect}}
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/ZioHttpServer/index.html}ZIO}}        | Integrate ZIO functional effects into OfficeFloor REST composition. | {{{https://zio.dev}ZIO}}
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


* Phase 3: Spring as Dependency Supplier

  In this phase OfficeFloor takes ownership of routing and composition while the existing framework continues to supply dependency-injected objects.  The step-by-step migration guides below show how to progressively move each framework's endpoints into OfficeFloor procedures, then remove the framework dependency entirely.


** Spring Web MVC

*-------+------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Step || Tutorial                                            || Description                                               || Covered
*-------+------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| 1     | {{{./spring_migration/SpringWebMvcHttpServer/index.html}Embed Spring Web MVC}} | Run Spring Web MVC @Controller within OfficeFloor. | Spring Web MVC @Controller
*-------+------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| 2     | {{{./spring_migration/SpringWebMvcHttpServer/procedure.html}Spring Web MVC Procedures}} | Integrate @Controller methods as OfficeFloor Procedures to start using IOCC features. | Spring Web MVC Procedure
*-------+------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| 3     | {{{./spring_migration/SpringWebMvcHttpServer/migrate.html}Migrate Spring Web MVC}} | Remove the Spring Web MVC dependency and run natively on OfficeFloor. | Migrate Spring Web MVC
*-------+------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


